habilidades_nomes: Run Away; Tinted Lens; Compound Eyes
habilidades_descricoes: Run Away allows the bearer to flee a battle with a wild Pokémon without fail, even if the opposing Pokémon has used a move like Mean Look or Bind , or has an ability such as Arena Trap . Pokémon with Run Away cannot switch out for another Pokémon, only flee. It does not allow the Pokémon to flee from Trainer battles.; Powers up “not very effective” moves.; Compound Eyes raises the ability-bearer's accuracy by 30%. In Generations 3-5 , this ability's name was formatted as Compoundeyes . If a Pokémon with Compound Eyes is first in the party, Pokémon that can be holding items have that chance increase from 50% to 60% (for common items), 5% to 20% (for uncommon items) or 1% to 5% (for rare items).

habilidades_nomes: Wonder Skin; Tinted Lens; Shield Dust
habilidades_descricoes: Wonder Skin halves the accuracy of all status moves targeted at the ability-bearer. It does not affect self-inflicted status moves like Reflect or Swords Dance , nor does it affect the secondary conditions of attacking moves like Flamethrower .; Powers up “not very effective” moves.; Blocks the added effects of attacks taken.

habilidades_nomes: Sand Force; Arena Trap; Sand Veil
habilidades_descricoes: Sand Force raises the power of Ground , Rock and Steel type moves by 30% during a sandstorm . It also grants immunity to the sandstorm damage, if not already immune (currently this only applies to Shellos since all other Pokémon with the ability are already immune).; Arena Trap prevents opponents from fleeing or switching out. Raised Pokémon are not affected. Raised Pokémon are any Flying types or those under the effects of Levitate , Magnet Rise or Telekinesis . Full details in glossary . If a Pokémon with Arena Trap is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are twice as likely to appear.; Sand Veil raises the ability-bearer's evasion by 20% in a sandstorm . It also gives immunity to sandstorm damage (if they are not already protected by being Ground / Rock / Steel type). If a Pokémon with Sand Veil is the leading party Pokémon while travelling in a sandstorm, wild Pokémon are only half as likely to appear.

Makes the foe nervous and unable to eat Berries.; Technician increases the power of moves - that are usually base power 60 or below - by 50%. Moves with variable base power are boosted only when it is 60 or below. For example, if Magnitude hits at level 6 it will be boosted from 50 to 75, but level 7 will stay at 70 base power. Moves like Sonic Boom that deal fixed HP damage are not affected by Technician .; When another Pokémon on the field uses a single-use held item, a Pokémon with Pickup will obtain the used item (if they are not already holding anything) and it can be used again. Pokémon with Pickup will also obtain an item thrown at them with Fling (if they are not already holding anything). In Generations 3-4 , Pickup has no effect in battle. When a battle ends, any party Pokémon with Pickup has a 10% chance of picking up an item (if they are not already holding an item). Items picked up range from Potions, Great Balls, Ultra Balls and Rare Candies up to Leftovers and some TMs. Better items have a lower chance of being found; furthermore, higher-level Pokémon will obtain better items.

habilidades_descricoes: Boosts Attack when hit by a Grass-type move.; Armor Tail prevents the opponent from using any moves that have priority, such as Quick Attack .; Cud Chew causes the Pokémon to reuse an already consumed Berry at the end of the next turn.

When a Pokémon with Rattled is hit by a Bug , Ghost or Dark type move, its Speed is raised one stage (up to the usual maximum of +6 stages).; Run Away allows the bearer to flee a battle with a wild Pokémon without fail, even if the opposing Pokémon has used a move like Mean Look or Bind , or has an ability such as Arena Trap . Pokémon with Run Away cannot switch out for another Pokémon, only flee. It does not allow the Pokémon to flee from Trainer battles.; Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .

habilidades_nomes: Sheer Force; Snow Cloak; Thick Fat
habilidades_descricoes: Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Here are the moves that increase in power under Sheer Force , listed alphabetically:; Snow Cloak raises ability-bearer's evasion by 20% in a hail storm. It also gives immunity to damage by hail (if they are not already protected by being Ice type). If a Pokémon with Snow Cloak is the leading party Pokémon while travelling in a hail storm/blizzard, wild Pokémon are only half as likely to appear.; Thick Fat reduces the damage taken from Fire -type and Ice -type moves by 50%. Interestingly, many Pokémon possessing this ability already take reduced damage from those types. A Dewgong or Walrein with Thick Fat would take 1 ⁄ 8 normal damage when hit by an Ice-type move.

habilidades_descricoes: Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Snow Warning creates a hailstorm when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition. If multiple Pokémon with weather-generating abilities ( Snow Warning , Drizzle , Drought or Sand Stream ) enter the field on the same turn, each weather condition will activate consecutively, fastest Pokémon first. In other words, the resultant weather condition will be that of the slowest Pokémon. Prior to Generation 6 , Snow Warning lasts indefinitely upon activation.; Refrigerate causes all Normal -type attacking moves used by the Pokémon to become Ice -type, and increase in power by 20%. Ice-type Pokémon also gain STAB from those moves (which means an effective increase of 80%). In Generation 6 , Refrigerate increases affected moves' power by 30%.

Mold Breaker prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Mold Breaker Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves. For example, a Haxorus with Mold Breaker would be able to hit a Bronzong (having Levitate ) using a Ground type move like Earthquake . Ground type moves would still not affect Flying types. However, if Dragon Claw KOs a Pokémon with Aftermath , a Mold Breaker Pokémon would still lose HP as Aftermath did not affect the Dragon Claw attack itself.; Raises Speed if a held item is used.; The Pokémon is protected from paralysis.

Stance Change is exclusive to Aegislash . When using a damage-dealing move, Aegislash switches to its Blade Forme. When using the move King's Shield , Aegislash switches to its Shield Forme. The form change occurs when the appropriate move is selected, regardless of whether the attack goes ahead (e.g. prevented by paralysis).

No Guard ensures that all attacks used by, and targeted at, the ability-bearer hit without fail. This includes moves used on a Pokémon in the hidden stages of the moves Fly , Dive , Dig and Shadow Force . If a Pokémon with No Guard is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are twice as likely to appear.

Download raises either the bearer's Attack or Special Attack by one stage when switching into battle, base on the opponent's defenses. It raises Attack if the opponent's Defense is lower than its Special Defense, or raises Special Attack if opponent's Special Defense is lower than or equal to its Defense. In double and triple battles, Download compares the sum of all opponents' Defense stats and the sum of all opponents' Special Defense stats and uses the lowest total.

Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .

Justified raises the ability-bearer's Attack by one stage when hit by a damaging Dark -type move. The Attack rises for every hit of the move Beat Up . Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each.

Pressure makes any attack targeted at the ability-bearer - regardless of whether it hits - use 2 PP instead of 1. If a Pokémon with Pressure is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are 50% more likely to be higher level.

However, using Dragon Claw against a Pokémon with Aftermath would still receive HP loss as Aftermath did not affect the Dragon Claw attack itself.

Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. If a Pokémon with Truant uses a move that requires recharging on the second turn (such as Hyper Beam ), it will recharge on the same turn the Pokémon loafs around. Moves where the user prepares on the first turn and attacks on the second (such as Solarbeam or Fly ) cannot be used. The moves Worry Seed , Entrainment and Simple Beam do not work on Pokémon with Truant . Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .; Boosts Attack when hit by a Grass-type move.; Chlorophyll doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during bright sunshine .

When a Pokémon with the Illusion ability switches into battle, it takes the form of the Pokémon in last place (6th) of the player's party. Illusion will not activate if the Pokémon in last place is the same species or is fainted. The effect is aesthetic only; Illusion does not change the Pokémon's type or moves, so for example a Fighting -type move against a Zoroark disguised as Gengar would still be super effective. Any direct attack (i.e. not entry hazards, weather conditions etc) will break the illusion .

Storm Drain forces all single-target Water -type moves - used by any other Pokémon on the field - to target this Pokémon, and with 100% accuracy. The ability is most useful in double/triple battles. Mold Breaker prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Mold Breaker Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves. The Simple ability doubles the number of stages of all stat changes. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each, or lowered to a minimum of -6 stages each. For example, using Swords Dance would increase the Pokémon's attack by 4 stages instead of the usual 2. If Tail Whip was targeted at a Pokémon with Simple , its Defense would drop 2 stages instead of 1. The move Simple Beam can change a Pokémon's ability to Simple . In Generation 4 , Simple doubles the effects of stat changes but does not increase the actual number of stages. Stat increases are capped at the same multiplier of ×4, as per the table below. However, the resulting effect is exactly the same as current games.; The Pokémon can't use any held items.; Ignores any stat changes in the Pokémon.

Super Luck raises the ability-bearer's critical-hit ratio by one stage (for most moves this increases from a 1 ⁄ 16 chance to 1 ⁄ 8 ).; Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .; Hustle increases the ability-bearer's Attack by 50%, however, it also reduces the Accuracy of all Physical moves by 20%. If a Pokémon with Hustle is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are 50% more likely to be higher level.

A Pokémon with Gluttony will use a pinch berry when its HP drops to 50%, rather than the usual 25%. Pinch berries are: Figy, Wiki, Mago, Aguav, Iapapa, Liechi, Ganlon, Salac, Petaya, Apicot, Lansat, Starf, Micle and Custap. (Their descriptions state that they work in a pinch. ); Thick Fat reduces the damage taken from Fire -type and Ice -type moves by 50%. A Dewgong or Walrein with Thick Fat would take 1 ⁄ 8 normal damage when hit by an Ice-type move.; When another Pokémon on the field uses a single-use held item, a Pokémon with Pickup will obtain the used item (if they are not already holding anything) and it can be used again. Pokémon with Pickup will also obtain an item thrown at them with Fling (if they are not already holding anything). In Generations 3-4 , Pickup has no effect in battle. When a battle ends, any party Pokémon with Pickup has a 10% chance of picking up an item (if they are not already holding an item). Items picked up range from Potions, Great Balls, Ultra Balls and Rare Candies up to Leftovers and some TMs. Better items have a lower chance of being found; furthermore, higher-level Pokémon will obtain better items.

Prankster increases the priority of status moves by +1. This means that a slower Pokémon with Prankster can use a status move before the opponent uses a regular move. Or if the ability-bearer is faster, it could use a status move before the opponent uses a priority move like Aqua Jet . The move Quick Guard does not block moves whose priority is increased by Prankster (but it does block moves that already have increased priority).; Inner Focus prevents the Pokémon from flinching, for example when attacked by a move like Headbutt .; Raises Speed each time the Pokémon flinches.

habilidades_descricoes: Sand Force raises the power of Ground , Rock and Steel type moves by 30% during a sandstorm . The ability is most useful in double/triple battles. When hit by the move, it deals no damage to the ability-bearer but raises its Special Attack by one stage. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each. Storm Drain will activate for an Water-type Hidden Power , but not Water-type Judgment . The ability is overridden by other Pokémon becoming the center of attention from the moves Follow Me or Rage Powder . In Generation 4 , Storm Drain did not increase Special Attack nor give immunity to Water-type attacks. It also did not activate for Hidden Power .; Sticky Hold prevents held items from being taken or switched. If a Pokémon with Sticky Hold is the leading party Pokémon, the chance of hooking a Pokémon during fishing increases.

Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Here are the moves that increase in power under Sheer Force , listed alphabetically:; Mold Breaker prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Mold Breaker Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves. For example, a Haxorus with Mold Breaker would be able to hit a Bronzong (having Levitate ) using a Ground type move like Earthquake . Ground type moves would still not affect Flying types. However, if Dragon Claw KOs a Pokémon with Aftermath , a Mold Breaker Pokémon would still lose HP as Aftermath did not affect the Dragon Claw attack itself.

Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .
Air Lock suppresses all effects brought on by weather, including move power increases, end-of-turn damage, accuracy changes, relevant abilities and so on.

Drought creates harsh sunlight when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition. If multiple Pokémon with weather-generating abilities ( Drought , Drizzle , Sand Stream or Snow Warning ) enter the field on the same turn, each weather condition will activate consecutively, fastest Pokémon first. In other words, the resultant weather condition will be that of the slowest Pokémon. Prior to Generation 6 , Drought lasts indefinitely upon activation.

Drizzle creates a rain shower when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition. In other words, the resultant weather condition will be that of the slowest Pokémon. Prior to Generation 6 , Drizzle lasts indefinitely upon activation.

Wonder Guard prevents damage from direct attacks unless they are super-effective. Shedinja is the only Pokémon to have this ability so this means that only Fire , Flying , Rock , Ghost and Dark moves will have an effect. However, Pokémon protected by Wonder Guard are not immune to indirect attacks. Status-category moves still work and all end-of-turn damage will still incur, for example from poisoning, burns, sandstorms or hail. Entry hazards such as Spikes or Stealth Rock will also damage Pokémon with Wonder Guard switching in. Attacks that do not take their type in account will also hit, such as Struggle , Beat Up or Future Sight . Since Shedinja only has 1 HP, any of the above damage will result in an instant knockout.

Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Here are the moves that increase in power under Sheer Force , listed alphabetically:; Guts raises the ability-bearer's Attack by 50% when inflicted by a major status ailment (poison, burn, paralysis, freeze or sleep). If burnt, the Pokémon does not suffer the usual drop in Attack. All other effects of the status condition remain, e.g. losing HP each turn (poison, burn), speed drop (paralysis) or being unable to attack (paralysis, freeze, sleep).; Thick Fat reduces the damage taken from Fire -type and Ice -type moves by 50%. Interestingly, many Pokémon possessing this ability already take reduced damage from those types. A Dewgong or Walrein with Thick Fat would take 1 ⁄ 8 normal damage when hit by an Ice-type move.

Sand Force raises the power of Ground , Rock and Steel type moves by 30% during a sandstorm . Truant causes the ability-bearer to only attack every alternate turn. On the even turns, it will say the Pokémon is loafing around . If a Pokémon with Truant uses a move that requires recharging on the second turn (such as Hyper Beam ), it will recharge on the same turn the Pokémon loafs around. Moves where the user prepares on the first turn and attacks on the second (such as Solarbeam or Fly ) cannot be used. The moves Worry Seed , Entrainment and Simple Beam do not work on Pokémon with Truant . Truant can technically be Skill Swapped away, however neither Slakoth, Slaking or Durant learn it.

May heal an ally's status conditions.; Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .; All status problems heal when it switches out.

habilidades_descricoes: Reduces damage done to allies.; Magic Guard protects the Pokémon from indirect damage, including: It does not prevent damage from confusion, trapping moves (e.g. Bind ) or Struggle . Infatuated Pokémon have a 50% chance of being immobilized by love each turn and unable to attack. If a Pokémon with Cute Charm is the leading party Pokémon, the chance of encountering a Pokémon of the opposite gender is 2 ⁄ 3 .

Super Luck raises the ability-bearer's critical-hit ratio by one stage (for most moves this increases from a 1 ⁄ 16 chance to 1 ⁄ 8 ).; Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .; Hustle increases the ability-bearer's Attack by 50%, however, it also reduces the Accuracy of all Physical moves by 20%. If a Pokémon with Hustle is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are 50% more likely to be higher level.

If Sturdy activates before the final hit of a multi-hit move (such as Fury Swipes ), the subsequent hit will still deal damage and therefore cause the Pokémon to faint. Drizzle creates a rain shower when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition. If multiple Pokémon with weather-generating abilities ( Drizzle , Drought , Sand Stream or Snow Warning ) enter the field on the same turn, each weather condition will activate consecutively, fastest Pokémon first. In other words, the resultant weather condition will be that of the slowest Pokémon. Prior to Generation 6 , Drizzle lasts indefinitely upon activation.; Damp prevents all Pokémon on the field from using the moves Selfdestruct and Explosion . It also prevents damage (to the Damp Pokémon only) from the ability Aftermath .; A Pokémon with Water Absorb heals 1 ⁄ 4 of its maximum HP when hit by a Water -type attack.

Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. When hit by the move, it deals no damage to the ability-bearer but raises its Special Attack by one stage. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each. Lightning Rod will activate for an Electric-type Hidden Power , but not Electric-type Judgment . The ability is overridden by other Pokémon becoming the center of attention from the moves Follow Me or Rage Powder . In Generations 3-4 , Lightning Rod did not increase Special Attack nor give immunity to Electric-type attacks. It also did not activate for Hidden Power . In Generations 3-5 , this ability's name was formatted as Lightningrod .; Prevents the Pokémon from getting a burn.; Swift Swim doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during rain .

Boosts move power when the Pokémon moves last.; All status problems heal when it switches out.; Illuminate has no effect in battle. If a Pokémon with Illuminate is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are twice as likely to appear.

Technician increases the power of moves - that are usually base power 60 or below - by 50%. Moves with variable base power are boosted only when it is 60 or below. For example, if Magnitude hits at level 6 it will be boosted from 50 to 75, but level 7 will stay at 70 base power. Moves like Sonic Boom that deal fixed HP damage are not affected by Technician .; Filter reduces the damage taken from super-effective attacks by 25%. For example, a Dark-type move used against a Psychic-type Pokémon with Filter would deal 1.5× the usual damage instead of 2×. A double weakness would be reduced from 4× to 3×.; Soundproof grants the Pokémon immunity to all sound-based moves, preventing all damage and effects. In Generation 5 only, Pokémon with Soundproof could be cured of status conditions by Heal Bell .

Moves like Sonic Boom that deal fixed HP damage are not affected by Technician .; Swarm increases the power of Bug -type moves by 50% (1.5×) when the ability-bearer's HP falls below a third of its maximum (known in-game as in a pinch ). If a Pokémon with Swarm is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are twice as likely to appear.

Vital Spirit prevents the ability-bearer from falling asleep. This means that it also prevents the use of the move Rest . If a Pokémon with Vital Spirit is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are 50% more likely to be higher level.; If a Pokémon with Static is hit by a move making contact, there is a 30% chance the foe will become paralyzed. If a Pokémon with Static is the leading party Pokémon, it is 50% more likely that a wild Pokémon encountered will be Electric type.

Vital Spirit prevents the ability-bearer from falling asleep. This means that it also prevents the use of the move Rest . If a Pokémon with Flame Body (or Magma Armor or Steam Engine ) and a Pokémon Egg are both in the party Pokémon, the number of steps required to hatch the egg are halved.

Moxie increases the user's Attack one stage upon fainting an opponent. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each.; Mold Breaker prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Mold Breaker Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves. For example, a Haxorus with Mold Breaker would be able to hit a Bronzong (having Levitate ) using a Ground type move like Earthquake . Ground type moves would still not affect Flying types. However, if Dragon Claw KOs a Pokémon with Aftermath , a Mold Breaker Pokémon would still lose HP as Aftermath did not affect the Dragon Claw attack itself.; Hyper Cutter prevents the bearer's Attack stat from being lowered by other Pokémon, through moves such as Growl or abilities such as Intimidate . It does not prevent self-inflicted decreases, for example from Superpower .

Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Stats can be lowered to a minimum of -6 stages each. If a Pokémon with Intimidate is the leading party Pokémon, wild Pokémon are 50% less likely to be lower level.

May heal an ally's status conditions.; Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance). Serene Grace does not affect status moves or the Pokémon's critical hit ratio. Shadow Ball normally has a 20% chance of lowering Special Defense; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 40% chance. Air Slash has a 30% of causing the target to flinch; with Serene Grace it is boosted to a 60% chance. If the item King's Rock is held it does not increase that percentage, but rather if the move does not cause flinching (40% chance), then there is now a further 20% chance the target will flinch from King's Rock . This means Serene Grace with Air Slash and King's Rock gives a total probability of 68% (1 - 0.4*0.8) that the opponent will flinch. In Generations 3-4 Serene Grace does not increase the flinch chance of King's Rock or Razor Fang. In Generations 3-5 Serene Grace does not affect the move Secret Power .; All status problems heal when it switches out.

A Pokémon with Regenerator restores 1 ⁄ 3 of its maximum HP when switching out.; Leaf Guard prevents the bearer from succumbing to major status ailments (sleep, burns, poisoning, paralysis or freezing) during sunny weather. It does not prevent minor status ailments such as Confusion or Infatuation, nor does it prevent self-inflicted status conditions such as from using Rest .; Chlorophyll doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during bright sunshine .
Inner Focus prevents the Pokémon from flinching, for example when attacked by a move like Headbutt .; Enables moves to hit Ghost-type Pokémon.; The Pokémon awakens quickly from sleep.

This means a critical hit will deal 2.25× normal damage instead of 1.5×. In Generations 1-5 critical hits deal 2× normal damage, so Sniper inflicts 3× normal damage.; Swift Swim doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during rain .

habilidades_nomes: Flame Body; Flash Fire; Run Away
habilidades_descricoes: If a Pokémon with Flame Body is hit by a move that makes contact, there is a 30% chance the attacker will become burned. If a Pokémon with Flame Body (or Magma Armor or Steam Engine ) and a Pokémon Egg are both in the party Pokémon, the number of steps required to hatch the egg are halved.; When a Pokémon with Flash Fire is hit by a Fire-type move, it does not deal damage but instead raises the power of the bearer's Fire-type moves by 50%. Subsequent hits do not raise the power even more, but the effect remains while the ability-bearer is in battle.; Run Away allows the bearer to flee a battle with a wild Pokémon without fail, even if the opposing Pokémon has used a move like Mean Look or Bind , or has an ability such as Arena Trap . Pokémon with Run Away cannot switch out for another Pokémon, only flee. It does not allow the Pokémon to flee from Trainer battles.

Magic Guard protects the Pokémon from indirect damage, including: It does not prevent damage from confusion, trapping moves (e.g. Bind ) or Struggle . In Generation 4 a Pokémon with Magic Guard cannot be poisoned from Toxic Spikes , nor become fully immobile through paralysis (though the Speed drop still occurs).; Inner Focus prevents the Pokémon from flinching, for example when attacked by a move like Headbutt .; If the opponent causes a burn, paralysis, or poisoning of a Pokémon with Synchronize , the opponent receives the status condition too. Self-inflicted status conditions (for example through the use of an item) are not passed on. In Generations 3-4 , bad poison is only passed on as regular poison. If a Pokémon with Synchronize is the leading party Pokémon, there is a 50% chance of each wild Pokémon encountered having the same nature.

Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects. Beneficial effects are defined as those that are positive for the user, such as: Non-beneficial effects, that Sheer Force will not activate for, include: If the user is holding a Life Orb and uses an attack that activates Sheer Force , it will not receive the 10% damage from Life Orb , but it gets boosts from both Life Orb and Sheer Force (total of 69% base power increase). Flamethrower normally has a 10% chance to burn the opponent. With Sheer Force , Flamethrower's base power is boosted from 95 to 124, but it will never cause a burn. Note that if a move has an advantageous and disadvantageous side-effect, Sheer Force still boosts the move but only the advantageous effect is removed. For example, Flare Blitz may cause a burn but also has recoil damage. A Pokémon with Sheer Force using the move would gain the power increase and still receive recoil damage, but it would never cause a burn. Lightning Rod forces all single-target Electric -type moves - used by any other Pokémon on the field - to target this Pokémon, and with 100% accuracy. This includes the status move Thunder Wave . The ability is most useful in double/triple battles. When hit by the move, it deals no damage to the ability-bearer but raises its Special Attack by one stage. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each. Lightning Rod will activate for an Electric-type Hidden Power , but not Electric-type Judgment . The ability is overridden by other Pokémon becoming the center of attention from the moves Follow Me or Rage Powder . In Generations 3-4 , Lightning Rod did not increase Special Attack nor give immunity to Electric-type attacks. It also did not activate for Hidden Power . In Generations 3-5 , this ability's name was formatted as Lightningrod .; If a Pokémon with Static is hit by a move making contact, there is a 30% chance the foe will become paralyzed. If a Pokémon with Static is the leading party Pokémon, it is 50% more likely that a wild Pokémon encountered will be Electric type.
